<figureCitation id="136C08C0FFEFC86CFD87BAE0FDA4FF0F" box="[541,629,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–21" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[490,1096,304,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-28@15.[490,1098,304,1940]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 20–21. Drymeia setibasis (Huckett), ♂ habitus. 20. Lateral view. 21. Dorsal view. (Georgia, Kazbegi, Gergeti scree (1), 2950–3000 m, 14.vii.1983.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538229/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="372">Figs 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136C08C0FFEFC86CFD1ABAE0FD71FF0F" box="[640,672,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–25" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1344,192,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-38@16.[236,1352,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 22–25. Drymeia setibasis (Huckett). 22. ♂ head, lateral view. 23. ♂ mid femur, anterior view. 24. ♀ mid femur, an- terior view. 25. ♂ hind tibia and tarsomere 1, anterior view. Scale-line 1 mm (3) and 0.5 mm (4–6). (Georgia, Kazbegi, Gergeti, scree &amp; river, 2950–3200 m, 11.vii.1983.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538231/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="372">23</figureCitation>
